For loops are used when the number of iterations is known beforehand, while while loops are used when the number of iterations is not known beforehand.

For example, if you want to print the numbers 1 through 5, you would use a for loop:

```
for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
  console.log(i);
}
```

If you want to print all the even numbers between 1 and 10, you would use a while loop:

```
let i = 1;

while (i <= 10) {
  if (i % 2 === 0) {
    console.log(i);
  }
  i++;
}
```

In general, for loops are more concise and easier to read, while while loops are more flexible and can handle more complex cases. It is important to choose the right type of loop for the specific use case.

